
[1]chafe

   CHAFE, v.t.

   1. To excite heat or inflammation by friction, as to chafe the skin;
   also, to fret and wear by rubbing, as to chafe a cable.

   2. To act violently upon, by rubbing; to fret against, as waves against
   a shore.

   The troubled Tyber chafing with his shores.

   3. To be fretted and worn by rubbing; as, a cable chafes.

                                  CHAFE, n.

   1. Heat, excited by friction.

   2. Violent agitation of the mind or passions; heat; fret; passion.
